08/06/2004
PORTOROZ, Slovenia -- The member states and organisations of the Stability Pact for South Eastern Europe kicked off their 5th Working and Regional Table Meetings in Portoroz on Monday (7 June). The two-day session marks the 5th anniversary of the establishment of the regional initiative for peace and security. In all, 300 people from 65 countries and organisations are participating. They are discussing media freedom, the role of parliaments in the democratic processes, and illegal migration. (Stability Pact Web site, HINA - 07/06/04)
